		<p>Hi Elise!  I love your blog.  I made the ice cream and caramel sauce the other day and they are great!  However, my caramel sauce had a really thick consistency.  If I wanted to make it thinner, do I just add more cream during the cooking process?  Thank you!</p>

<p><em>Note from Elise: The caramel was really thick even when warm? The sauce should be warmed before serving - the heat will make it much runnier. If heat isn't the issue, then I suppose you could try adding more cream.</em></p>	
