		<p>Very very tasty!<br />
Just a few pointers for people who are going to make this:<br />
1) Make sure you do not burn the sugar! If you burn the sugar, then the end product will taste burnt. I suggest when there are still a few sugar clumps in the pot, immediately add the butter and immediately take off the element.  If you do burn it slightly, then add a few teaspoons of vanilla extract.<br />
2) Add 1 tablespoon or so of cocoa powder if you like chocolate. This also decreases the taste of burn if you have slightly burnt it.</p>

