	<div class="comment" id="c110855">
		<p>I was looking for a caramel sauce recipe for my mango crepe. I decided to use your recipe. I was wondering what type of butter you use- salted or unsalted? Also, how do you measure the butter? Should you melt it on a saucepan first? Thank you.</p>

<p><em>Usually I use unsalted butter for everything, however in this recipe, caramel does benefit from a little added salt (think salted caramels), so if you have it, I would use salted butter.  Most butter comes in sticks with the measurements listed on the side of the stick.  You can also measure it by scooping it into a measuring cup.  Should you melt it in a saucepan first? No, that isn't necessary. ~Elise</em></p>	
	</div>
